cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human perception of visual data and proposes a new algorithm for detecting and grouping features in random dot videos. The use of statistical tests and the a contrario framework also suggests a machine learning (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.LG) approach. Additionally, the proposal of a computational Gestalt model of human perception implies an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) aspect. Finally, the use of visual angle as a parameter suggests a graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
